Colombia’s Aval Rises as Chairman Allowed to Acquire Stock

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-18T20:19:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/colombia-s-grupo-aval-rises-as-chairman-allowed-to-acquire-stock.html
Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA,
 Colombia ’s biggest financial holding company, rose after the
company’s board of directors gave chairman Luis Carlos Sarmiento Angulo permission to acquire shares.  Sarmiento can acquire common or preferred shares worth up
to 30 billion pesos ($16.5 million), according to a regulatory
filing today. Preferred shares rose 2.8 percent to 1,300 pesos
at 4 p.m. New York time, after rising to as much as 1,305 pesos
earlier. Common shares rose 1 percent to 1,290 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
